UNDIAGNOSED FATAL DISEASE, BOVINE - LAOS (02): (CHAMPASSAK) RFI
***************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

******
[1]
Date: Fri 11 Feb 2011
Source: KPL Lao News Agency via Laovoices.com [edited]
<http://laovoices.com/2011/02/11/foot-and-mouth-disease-kills-over-1600-cattle-in-champassak-province/>


Foot-and-mouth disease kills over 1600 cattle in Champassak province
--------------------------------------------------------------------
More than 1600 head of cattle have been killed in the past one month
in the 10 districts of Champassak province. According to a source from
this southernmost province, today the outbreak of the disease has
declined.

The Livestock and Fishery Division, Agriculture and Forestry Service
of Champassak province, disclosed on 2 Feb 2011 that the province
dispatched its technical officers to work with local farmers at
villages in the districts to help them combat the outbreak of the
disease.

The limit in funding and necessary equipment was attributed to the
main cause of the outbreak, said the Livestock and Fishery Division.

